4
00:01:37,249 --> 00:01:40,589
(After driving for 7 hours,
he arrives at a cliff.)

5
00:01:41,690 --> 00:01:43,350
Oh, someone's coming.

6
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:45,990
(Someone is flying...)

7
00:01:45,990 --> 00:01:46,990
Who is it?

8
00:01:46,990 --> 00:01:48,289
(across the giant cliff.)

9
00:01:48,289 --> 00:01:49,490
It's like Tarzan.

10
00:01:51,359 --> 00:01:53,159
Someone's coming on the zipline.

11
00:01:53,900 --> 00:01:55,629
(Doubting his eyes)

12
00:01:55,999 --> 00:01:58,539
(A man is coming across the scary cliff.)

13
00:01:59,870 --> 00:02:00,909
Hello.

14
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,070
Hello.

15
00:02:04,779 --> 00:02:06,610
(He quickly lands on the other side.)

16
00:02:06,909 --> 00:02:07,949
Hello.

17
00:02:07,949 --> 00:02:09,949
- Hello. How are you?
- Hello. How are you?

18
00:02:09,949 --> 00:02:12,919
- I'm good.
- I'm good.

19
00:02:13,479 --> 00:02:15,589
- Kian84.
- Kian84.

20
00:02:15,589 --> 00:02:17,290
- Yes. Kian84.
- Yes.

21
00:02:17,290 --> 00:02:21,659
- I live over there. It's my house.
- Yes. My house.

22
00:02:21,659 --> 00:02:24,659
- I use this to go across.
- I see.

23
00:02:24,659 --> 00:02:26,500
It's my form of transportation.

24
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,669
- Transportation.
- Transportation.

25
00:02:28,669 --> 00:02:31,300
- You? Here?
- Yes.

26
00:02:32,399 --> 00:02:33,869
Gosh. They're like stairs.

27
00:02:33,869 --> 00:02:36,409
Since there are a lot of mountains,
there are a lot of people...

28
00:02:36,409 --> 00:02:37,879
who farm and live on ridges.

29
00:02:37,879 --> 00:02:39,879
(For them, the zipline
is a form of transportation...)

30
00:02:39,879 --> 00:02:41,980
Gosh. They also send things on it.

31
00:02:41,980 --> 00:02:43,250
(and a form of communication
that connects them to the world.)

32
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:47,420
It's because this connects
right to my house.

33
00:02:47,489 --> 00:02:48,489
(House, Current location)

34
00:02:48,489 --> 00:02:52,289
(The zipline connects his house
directly to the big road.)

35
00:02:53,220 --> 00:02:56,289
His house
is right in front of the zipline.

36
00:02:56,289 --> 00:02:58,230
- Like a house next to a station.
- Exactly. A station district.

37
00:02:58,230 --> 00:02:59,629
- A zipline district.
- A zipline district.

38
00:02:59,830 --> 00:03:02,700
So each house has a zipline.

39
00:03:02,700 --> 00:03:04,470
- They're privately owned
- Really?

40
00:03:04,470 --> 00:03:06,200
- It's like having your own car.
- I see.

41
00:03:06,200 --> 00:03:08,539
I see. They each have a zipline.

42
00:03:08,869 --> 00:03:10,739
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

43
00:03:10,980 --> 00:03:12,580
To your house.

44
00:03:12,580 --> 00:03:14,080
How old are you?

45
00:03:15,580 --> 00:03:17,050
I can't speak English.

46
00:03:17,349 --> 00:03:18,619
No English?

47
00:03:18,720 --> 00:03:19,750
Okay.

48
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:22,849
I translated some things,
so I should try to say those.

49
00:03:22,849 --> 00:03:24,119
(Kian84 finally meets a local friend
after driving for seven hours.)

50
00:03:24,860 --> 00:03:26,560
How old are you?

51
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:35,399
How is his age so long?

52
00:03:35,399 --> 00:03:36,529
(His age sounds quite long.)

53
00:03:37,399 --> 00:03:38,769
