54
00:03:40,269 --> 00:03:41,769
Oh, it's kind of philosophical.

55
00:03:42,969 --> 00:03:43,980
One more.

56
00:03:44,540 --> 00:03:45,839
One second.

57
00:03:46,339 --> 00:03:48,350
I'm 38 years old.

58
00:03:50,149 --> 00:03:52,019
Oh, you're 38 years old?

59
00:03:52,719 --> 00:03:55,050
- Your birthday...
- You?

60
00:03:56,249 --> 00:03:58,619
I'm 39.

61
00:03:59,519 --> 00:04:00,890
- Yes.
- Okay.

62
00:04:00,890 --> 00:04:02,529
- You're younger, then.
- He's younger?

63
00:04:02,660 --> 00:04:04,399
- Okay.
- You're my brother.

64
00:04:05,559 --> 00:04:08,300
(They quickly figure out their
respective ranks, Korean style.)

65
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:09,330
Brother.

66
00:04:09,330 --> 00:04:12,399
You'll be able to see lots
of fun things at my house.

67
00:04:13,070 --> 00:04:15,269
(Using body language)

68
00:04:15,269 --> 00:04:16,339
Alegre?

69
00:04:17,410 --> 00:04:18,679
Okay, thank you.

70
00:04:18,679 --> 00:04:20,350
- I'm sure he said something nice.
- Thank you.

71
00:04:20,350 --> 00:04:21,410
Thank you.

72
00:04:21,910 --> 00:04:23,580
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

73
00:04:23,580 --> 00:04:25,519
(Kian84 heads straight to the zipline.)

74
00:04:25,519 --> 00:04:26,880
- What are you doing?
- Are you going to ride it?

75
00:04:28,890 --> 00:04:32,459
- We're going around by car.
- Oh, I see.

76
00:04:32,459 --> 00:04:33,730
Oh, you're going in the car.

77
00:04:33,730 --> 00:04:34,730
(Slightly disappointed)

78
00:04:34,730 --> 00:04:35,760
Okay.

79
00:04:37,029 --> 00:04:38,959
I wanted to ride that,

80
