they thought it might be dangerous.

84
00:04:48,239 --> 00:04:49,410
- That's true.
- True. Who knows what might happen?

85
00:04:50,209 --> 00:04:53,580
(It takes approximately 20 seconds
on zipline.)

86
00:04:54,510 --> 00:04:58,279
(They go by car to be safe...)

87
00:04:58,980 --> 00:05:04,559
(and walk the rest of the way
where the car can't go.)

88
00:05:05,189 --> 00:05:07,189
Put on your seat belt.

89
00:05:08,890 --> 00:05:10,429
- I see.
- Here.

90
00:05:10,959 --> 00:05:13,600
(So kind.)

91
00:05:14,670 --> 00:05:16,999
You don't speak English?

92
00:05:18,769 --> 00:05:20,100
(The Spanish notes he's been studying)

93
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:21,709
You've been studying.

94
00:05:21,709 --> 00:05:23,170
I wanted to communicate with people a bit.

95
00:05:23,170 --> 00:05:24,480
Oh, okay.

96
00:05:25,239 --> 00:05:26,439
What's your name?

97
00:05:26,980 --> 00:05:29,910
Celso Porfirio Cordero Liberos.

98
00:05:32,580 --> 00:05:33,820
I'll write it.

99
00:05:35,589 --> 00:05:36,820
Okay.

100
00:05:37,489 --> 00:05:38,589
Okay.

101
00:05:39,089 --> 00:05:41,830
Calso Porlilo...

102
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:44,429
- Porfirio.
- Porfilio.

103
00:05:44,730 --> 00:05:46,030
(Laughing)

104
00:05:46,030 --> 00:05:48,069
Porfirio.

105
00:05:48,069 --> 00:05:49,670
- Cordero.
- Cordero.

106
00:05:49,730 --> 00:05:51,800
- Celso.
- Your name...

107
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:54,809
is Celso Porfirio Cordero Liberos.

108
00:05:54,809 --> 00:05:56,809
- Nice.
- His name is quite long.

109
00:05:57,809 --> 00:06:00,650
(Actually, he said his name earlier.)

110
00:06:00,650 --> 00:06:01,879
Oh, that was his name.

111
00:06:02,350 --> 00:06:04,119
(Kian84 just didn't understand.)

112
00:06:04,449 --> 00:06:06,179
And your birthday...

113
00:06:06,780 --> 00:06:08,949
