114
00:06:09,819 --> 00:06:12,020
I was born in 1984.

115
00:06:12,389 --> 00:06:14,360
Your birthday.

116
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:16,059
It turns out, he was born in 1984.
He was the same age as me.

117
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:18,059
You're my friend.

118
00:06:18,059 --> 00:06:20,100
He's the same age as you.

119
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:21,429
My birthday.

120
00:06:21,900 --> 00:06:24,139
This is mine. Yes.

121
00:06:24,239 --> 00:06:25,300
You...

122
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:28,639
What month and date? I can't read it
if you write it in English.

123
00:06:29,739 --> 00:06:32,480
(He writes each letter
slowly, but carefully.)

124
00:06:32,579 --> 00:06:34,749
Oh, May 14th?

125
00:06:34,749 --> 00:06:36,379
- Okay.
- Porfi84.

126
00:06:36,850 --> 00:06:38,550
Gosh. Friend.

127
00:06:39,350 --> 00:06:41,590
- Same age.
- Yes.

128
00:06:41,590 --> 00:06:43,550
What are the chances
that you're the same age?

129
00:06:43,550 --> 00:06:45,559
It was interesting
that we were the same age.

130
00:06:45,689 --> 00:06:48,259
He's a friend of the same age
from the other side of the planet.

131
00:06:48,989 --> 00:06:50,290
It was cool.

132
00:06:50,290 --> 00:06:52,230
It was cute too.

133
00:06:52,429 --> 00:06:54,970
What were you doing during my interview?

134
00:06:54,970 --> 00:06:56,069
What is he doing?

135
00:06:56,270 --> 00:06:58,270
I was saying something important,
but he's so distracting.

136
00:06:58,270 --> 00:06:59,840
- He was sleeping over there.
- Yes.

137
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:01,309
He really takes the spotlight.

138
00:07:01,309 --> 00:07:04,139
Hey. Pani Bottle is packing back there.

139
00:07:04,139 --> 00:07:05,179
(Drying his socks)

140
00:07:05,340 --> 00:07:07,040
At least I was staying still.

141
00:07:07,139 --> 00:07:09,280
(Quietly stealing the spotlight)

142
00:07:09,780 --> 00:07:12,449
I'm solo.

143
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:15,389
- Me too.
- Solo.

144
00:07:16,319 --> 00:07:17,759
(Are you also single?)

145
00:07:17,759 --> 00:07:19,660
- You?
- I...

146
00:07:20,389 --> 00:07:22,129
(Writing his answer)

147
00:07:23,230 --> 00:07:24,629
Okay. Understand.

148
00:07:25,300 --> 00:07:27,369
He isn't married, but he has a wife?

149
00:07:27,629 --> 00:07:29,699
You haven't gotten married,
but you have a wife?

150
00:07:29,699 --> 00:07:31,300
That's what he said.

151
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:32,739
(Serious)

152
00:07:33,139 --> 00:07:34,239
What is this?

153
00:07:34,639 --> 00:07:35,869
Girlfriend?

154
00:07:35,869 --> 00:07:37,309
(What is this with this charismatic guy?)

155
00:07:38,239 --> 00:07:39,610
Did he get divorced?

156
00:07:40,579 --> 00:07:43,980
(He reveals his secret.)

157
00:07:44,420 --> 00:07:47,590
I haven't gotten married,
but I have a kid with her.

158
00:07:47,590 --> 00:07:49,720
- They haven't had a wedding ceremony.
- I understand.

159
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:52,020
Yes. That can happen.

160
00:07:52,220 --> 00:07:53,319
I'm jealous.

161
00:07:53,989 --> 00:07:57,189
Are you getting married in 2024?

162
00:07:58,429 --> 00:07:59,999
I should send some flowers.

163
00:08:00,970 --> 00:08:04,569
I won't be able to make it,
but I'll send some flowers.

164
00:08:05,670 --> 00:08:07,040
(I see.)

165
00:08:08,110 --> 00:08:10,139
(Sending a token of friendship
to the other side of the planet)

166
00:08:10,980 --> 00:08:13,110
That'd be crazy
if you actually sent him flowers.

167
00:08:13,110 --> 00:08:14,550
I can send some flowers.

168
00:08:14,980 --> 00:08:17,720
Your job?

169
00:08:18,220 --> 00:08:19,579
I am...

170
00:08:19,879 --> 00:08:21,550
a farmer. I see.

171
00:08:23,290 --> 00:08:26,319
My family...

172
00:08:26,889 --> 00:08:28,129
used to farm too.

173
00:08:28,790 --> 00:08:32,460
My family... Rice...

174
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:35,499
Do you know Korean...

175
00:08:35,499 --> 00:08:36,999
- Icheon?
- Icheon rice?

176
00:08:36,999 --> 00:08:40,239
Yeoju rice.

177
00:08:40,400 --> 00:08:42,910
- Yeoju rice.
- It's very famous.

178
00:08:43,809 --> 00:08:46,809
My...

179
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,379
Wait.

180
00:08:49,079 --> 00:08:52,749
My job is painting.

181
00:08:53,179 --> 00:08:55,119
- I see.
- Yes.

182
00:08:55,119 --> 00:08:57,559
Comic. Cartoon.

183
00:08:57,590 --> 00:09:00,559
- Spiderman. Batman. Superman.
- I see.

184
00:09:02,160 --> 00:09:03,290
"Fashion King."

185
00:09:06,699 --> 00:09:09,569
<i>BTS, Bong Joon Ho, Son Heung Min</i>

186
